Try to determine the network interface to use for add/remove multicast group membership from the bind address or the configured multicast interface. When none can be determined then fail with a proper async error message instead of failing with a synchronous NPE.

The FutureBase reports failure in FutureImpl emitSuccess/emitFailure methods along with the potential context dispatch. Instead this should be performed by the listener, multiple listeners will also each report error independantly and also be applied independantly on whether it required a context execution.

Fix regression in CLI introduced by 2f690d7d6420c3601b0d62eeb574cae6dc6b3426 that moved the VertxBuilder before the metrics options are initialized from the system properties which prevents metrics to be initialized from system properties - fixes #4008

Improve the HTTP/1.x request handling to route invalid requests to a new HttpServer invalid request handler. The policy used to directly send a Netty response through the pipeline and then report the error, the handling has been rewritten to instead call the new invalid request handler and when the response is sent then the connection is closed with the decoder result error. The existing policy has been rewritten to use Vert.x API instead instead of using a FullHttpResponse.

Fix a regression in CloseFuture: a finalized closeable resource might be removed from the hooks after the list is copied and the close future will not progress. The close hooks should be copied before.

The HTTP/2 connection metric is registered agains the TCP metrics when the HTTP/2 connection preface is received. When an HTTP/2 connection is closed before the connection preface is received, the TCP metrics is signaled the connection unregistration without a prior connection registration. As side effect his can lead to incorrect state in a metrics implementation, such as a negative connection count.
